<!--<h4><hi rend="italic">First Face.</hi></h4>-->

<p>
<lb n="1"/>svasti śrīmat sakalalōkāśrayajayasiṁgha
<lb n="2" break="no"/>vallabhamahārājulākuN pravarddhamānavijayarā
<lb n="3" break="no"/>jyasaṁvatsaraṁbuḷ EṇuṁbodiAnnēṇṭi Armmapūṇṇa
<lb n="4" break="no"/>manāṇḍuṁ mlāviṁḍirājulamuṭḷukalimuḍirājul
<lb n="5"/>mlāviṁḍisamudrarakai nāku baṇisēsina kalcivī
<lb n="6" break="no"/>ḻaruṟla madhdikadumūṭiki vitpaṟti Uttaraṁbuna pulo
<lb n="7" break="no"/>ṁbuna ceṟuvu paḍumāṟikōṭaN Eṇuṁbodi puṭḷu Ā
<lb n="8"/>ṛlapaṭṭusēnu <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> tūrppuna kōṭitā<unclear>ṟu</unclear>tōṁṭaḷāyu paḍuvā
<lb n="9" break="no"/>raṁbu Icciri pāṟapaḍuvāraṁbu mlāvi<unclear>ṁ</unclear>ḍīśvaraṁbuna kaḷā
<lb n="10" break="no"/>kaṇḍugumicci kuḍucuvāru yiṟlakānu Ē veṟuguvā
<lb n="11" break="no"/>ru vitpaṟtigāṇaṁbu<unclear>ndho</unclear>lgoṭṭa<unclear>na</unclear>ṁgāṇaṁbu cuvvuṭūrugāṇaṁbu<note n="208-1">The following four lines are cut below in the characters of the same type:— 

<l n="6:208:584:1"> <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> <unclear>vra</unclear>ccinavāru bārāṇasivēvru</l>

<l n="6:208:584:2"> <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> līḍisa<unclear>mu</unclear>draṁbu malā</l>

<l n="6:208:584:3"> <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> ḍisenavadiki</l>

<l n="6:208:584:4"> <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> ramañci</l></note>
</p>

<!--<h4><hi rend="italic">Second Face.</hi></h4>-->

<p>
<lb n="12"/> <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/> <unclear>bahubhi</unclear>rvvasu<unclear>dhā</unclear> da<unclear>ttā</unclear>
<lb n="13"/>bahubhiścānupālitā <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> yasya ya <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="14"/>dā bhūmi<unclear>ḥ</unclear> tasya tasya tadā pha <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="15"/>svadattaṁ paradattaṁ vā yō harēti va <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="16"/>ṣaṣṭhi<unclear>ṁ</unclear> varṣasahasrāṇi viṣṭhāyāṁ jāya <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="17"/><unclear>bhū</unclear>midānāt parandānaṁ na bhūtanna bhaviṣya<unclear>ti</unclear> <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied>
<lb n="18"/>tasyaiva vāraṇāt pāpanna bhūtanna bhaviṣyati [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g>]
<lb n="19"/>brahmasvaṁ ve<unclear>ṣa</unclear>saṁpannaṁ yō harēti ma<unclear>hī</unclear>patē
<lb n="20"/>tēṣāṁ <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> mēdhya <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/> mēdhya <gap reason="lost" quantity="5" unit="character"/> <note n="209-1">The rest of the inscription is damaged. On the left side of the slab are found the 

<l n="6:209:584:1">maḷavivisva</l>

<l n="6:209:584:2">ṁbusacāmavī</l>

<l n="6:209:584:3">nainyamākaḷi</l>

<l n="6:209:584:4">muḍasvarace</l></note>
</p>

